<subSubSection id="A1D565563F7DFFEAFF26FEC0FE17FC25" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F7DFFEAFF26FEC0FF00FDF5" blockId="72.[151,1437,290,964]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
Morphology. D VI + I,8–9; A I,8–9; P 17–19 (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F7DFFEAFD33FEC0FCBDFE81" author="Miller, P. J." box="[722,861,326,352]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="53 - 88" refId="ref61330" refString="Miller, P. J. (1973) The identity of Gobius affinis Kolombatovic, with notes on the systematics and biology of Pomatoschistus pictus (Malm). Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale ' Giacomo Doria', 79, 53 - 88." type="journal article" year="1973">Miller 1973</bibRefCitation>
). Moderately small goby with subcylindrical body, laterally compressed towards caudal fin, head slightly depressed and moderately large. Snout pointed, moderately large. Eyes dorsolateral, interorbital space narrow. Caudal peduncle deep, but lower than body depth. Dorsal fins of similar height, the first dorsal fin with more or less rounded margin and no elongated spines. Caudal fin rounded. Scales present on body, usually visible on photographs at least dorsally. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7DFFEAFC31FE50FB04FE0E" bold="true" box="[976,1252,469,496]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Predorsal area naked (</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F7DFFEAFB04FE51FF34FDF5" author="Ozturk, D. S. &amp; Engin, S." pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="142 - 150" refId="ref62441" refString="Ozturk, D. S. &amp; Engin, S. (2019) Taxonomic status of the Mediterranean-endemic goby Pomatoschistus adriaticus Miller, 1973 inferred with both morphological and genetic data. Zoology in the Middle East, 65, 142 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 09397140.2019.1580932" type="journal article" year="2019">Öztürk &amp; Engin 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F7DFFEAFF26FD98FBF3FCF1" blockId="72.[151,1437,290,964]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
Live coloration. Body pale gray to pale brown with 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7DFFEAFCE6FD98FAE5FDD9" bold="true" box="[775,1285,541,568]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">5 whitish saddles and dark mottled pattern</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F7DFFEAFAF5FD98FA86FDD8" box="[1300,1382,542,569]" captionStart="FIGURE 62" captionStartId="72.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,988,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-336@72.[151,1436,988,1844]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="FIGURE 62. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Pomatoschistus adriaticus. Photo by S. Guerrieri, Rijeka, Croatia, northern Adriatic Sea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601755" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601755/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
), the first narrow light saddle, at the origin of first dorsal fin, is followed by 2 broader ones below second dorsal fin, and 2 on caudal peduncle. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7DFFEAFE75FDE0FA75FD45" bold="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Body with 5 dark midlateral blotches, sometimes reduced to double black dots, extend from below the above light saddles, the last blotch appearing as a horizontal black mark on caudal-fin base</emphasis>
. Cheeks pale gray, with only scattered black dots. A dark patch around upper pectoral-fin base divides in 2 oblique branches over upper and lower opercle and preopercle. Dorsal fins with three horizontal pale brown to pinkish lines (often with rows of black dots) alternating with three whitish to light blue lines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F7DFFEAFF26FC9CFBC3FCD5" blockId="72.[151,1437,290,964]" box="[199,1059,794,820]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F7DFFEAFE9EFC9CFD90FCD5" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1982" box="[383,624,794,820]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Pomatoschistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bathi">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7DFFEAFE9EFC9CFD90FCD5" box="[383,624,794,820]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Pomatoschistus bathi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F7DFFEAFD9FFC9DFD00FCD5" authorityName="Engin &amp; Seyhan" authorityYear="2017" box="[638,736,794,820]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Pomatoschistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nanus">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7DFFEAFD9FFC9DFD6FFCD5" box="[638,655,795,820]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7DFFEAFD7CFC9DFD00FCD5" box="[669,736,795,820]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">nanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F7DFFEAFD0FFC9DFC76FCD5" authorityName="Benthic" baseAuthorityName="Risso" baseAuthorityYear="1810" box="[750,918,794,820]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Pomatoschistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marmoratus">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7DFFEAFD0FFC9DFD1FFCD5" box="[750,767,795,820]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7DFFEAFCECFC9DFC76FCD5" box="[781,918,795,820]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">marmoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F7DFFEAFC45FC9DFBFCFCD5" authorityName="Benthic" baseAuthorityName="Kroyer" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[932,1052,794,820]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Pomatoschistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microps">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7DFFEAFC45FC9DFC55FCD5" box="[932,949,795,820]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7DFFEAFC22FC9DFBFCFCD5" box="[963,1052,795,820]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">microps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F7DFFEAFF26FCB8FBFBFC9D" blockId="72.[151,1437,290,964]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
Habitat. Infralittoral species, on coarse sand containing biogenic calcareous fragments and shell gravel with coralline deposits (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F7DFFEAFE8BFCE5FD84FC9D" author="Ozturk, D. S. &amp; Engin, S." box="[362,612,866,894]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="142 - 150" refId="ref62441" refString="Ozturk, D. S. &amp; Engin, S. (2019) Taxonomic status of the Mediterranean-endemic goby Pomatoschistus adriaticus Miller, 1973 inferred with both morphological and genetic data. Zoology in the Middle East, 65, 142 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 09397140.2019.1580932" type="journal article" year="2019">Öztürk &amp; Engin 2019</bibRefCitation>
), sand at 
